The taxi that slammed into the tree.PHOTO: ER24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories A TAXI crashed into a tree on Boshoff Road, Pietermaritzburg, injuring 11 people on Monday morning.ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene to find that the occupants had already climbed out of the vehicle. The paramedics assessed the patients and discovered that three had sustained serious while eight others had sustained minor to moderate injuries.Paramedics from various services treated the patients and provided the seriously injured with advanced life support interventions.Once all the patients had been treated, they were transported to various provincial hospitals.The driver later told paramedics he had apparently lost control of the vehicle, causing it to crash into a tree.Local authorities will be conducting an investigation into this incident. - Supplied.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.